metadata.name: Classic Automaton #84
metadata.description:
This is classical Automaton for those who loves "automaton" [cellular automata algorithm] as it is. Black and white  representation of standard algorithm organized in "Classic Automaton" canvas based on selected rules and is "framed" in Automaton variation of rules in same time.

The basic proportion of result artwork is related to square, 2 squares and 0.5 squares as a tribute to the system of "double square" proportion scale.

- "Tap" or "Mouse Click" on screen to rebuild variation;
- Press "s" key on the keyboard to save generated result in maximum resolution possible 4096 or 8192 px depends on iteration`s proportion of the result canvas to lossless PNG image file.

*use the browser`s functionality to zoom and pan the canvas.

metadata.name: Cluster Waves #26
metadata.description:
"Cluster Waves" edition - is the next response to the pure wave generators in sound and visuals. Continuing an "independent room" sound installation based on visual attraction generated in real time by procedural technologies of generative sound and visual. 

Audio-visual Components:
Sine waves, sawtooth, rectangles, random, Pi, Mixolydian.


UI functionality 

- keys 1,2,3,4 are switching Pixel Cluster size (affects the PC rendering load)

- click/tap on screen to start play the audio if not started automatically (required on some browsers if sound is not started immediately)

- close the page to sound off 

- press "s" to save the frame as static image at the square size of the current browser`s window. (Open window at maximum possible size to save the possible maximum image)

* use this artwork on your own risk when you know what is the sound and visual affect on the physical world. 
** Created to show the pure sound beauty in connection with raw slow motion graphics.

metadata.name: Grid Field #47
metadata.description:
Grid of feels and Field of surround are linked to each others. The audiovisual abstraction is tuning the feels after and before the feels are linked to the surround and reconstructing the grid of perception by grinding the feels through the Grid Field. 

Abstract motion artwork is formed with  metric grid and is animated by cosine waves. 

The sound is generated with pure sine waves generators whose sound frequencies are setted in connection of dorian, ionian and phrygian tempered harmonic scales.

/

press "s" to save static frame

metadata.name: WAVE TONES #29
metadata.description:
The concept of "WAVE TONES" is taken from the previous release "DISCRETEw" in the chain, where the nature of waves interpolation demonstrates process of discretizing a constant single-tone wave into multiple moving block elements at different scales.

In the next "WAVE TONES" generation the algorithm is exploring Tones of  Wave and is connecting sound harmony and visual art in one by rescaling the geometry of waves according to harmonic frequencies of 3-tones for single wave.

The tuned Waves are representing result Tones visually by overlapping groups of Waving Tones in one geometric pattern.  

Separate composition in sound is based on random chords from another addition scales of sounding frequencies generated by independent sinewave generators. 

Few groups of overlapping visual tones of waves are combined with related sonic concept in sounding frequencies and the result composition is forming audio visual experience of "WAVE TONES"

UI features: 
press "g" to record 360 frames loop gif animation at the current window size. 
press "s" to save current static frame in png image.

(p) V4W.ENKO at FXHash.xyz 2025

metadata.name: HERE & NOW PORTALS #357
metadata.description:
The 'Portal' is your gateway to 'The Passage' created by HERE & NOW. This interactive minting project seeks to transform the traditional minting experience into something truly unique and unexpected.

Each 'Portal' gives you access and 1x reserve for all future 'The Passage' experiences both virtual and IRL.

For more information, visit hereandnow.events or join the discord, and join us in redefining what it means to mint.

See LICENCE.md for license details.

TECHNOLOGY :::::::::

This token is designed using a custom-built raymarching engine, built in a way that allows me to pass in chunks of GLSL code as determined by the params and features.

The geometry is generated using what's called a KIFS (Kaleidoscopic Iterated Function System) fractal, which involves taking the space, folding it, offsetting it, drawing in it, and repeating. By doing this, we can create some *very* complex appearing geometry using some relatively simple rules.

Finally, this is an intense simulation and requires a somewhat powerful GPU to properly be enjoyed.

CONTROLS :::::::::::

Mouse - Click and drag to move the camera around in the space.
Q/E - Roll the camera.
R/F - Change the speed of the camera.
SPACE - Stop the camera from moving.
O - Output a still picture without DOF.
P - Output a still picture with DOF.

URL PARAMS :::::::::

&still=true
This will just render a still image.

&dpr=X
Where X is a number. Will allow you to render the token to a higher or lower resolution

&fullscreen=true
Allows you to render the token at the screen resolution of your browser.

&width=X &height=Y
Allows you to set the specific dimensions of the token.

&dof=true
Turns fake depth of field on.

&doflenngth=X
Changes the length at with the DOF is calculated.

&steps=X
Allows you to explicitly set the number of steps the raymarcher can use.
